# Thesis writing style

When editing `thesis/**/*.md`:

- Write in Polish academic style; match terminology in `thesis/GLOSSARY.md`
- Use paragraphs of 3–6 sentences; avoid bullet-only sections in final prose
- No marketing tone; describe IDA as a research prototype
- Institution: **Akademia Sztuki w Szczecinie** (never „Akademia Sztuk Pięknych”)
- Product name: **IDA** (Aura/AWA only as legacy code folder names, not product name)
- Stack: GCP for persistence and generation (not Supabase/Modal as production)
- Do not invent citations; use `[Autor, rok — DO UZUPEŁNIENIA]` placeholders
- Mark unverified implementation claims `[WERYFIKACJA_KOD]` until fact-checked
- Prefer `docs/canon/` and code over old README files for facts
- Output drafts for author revision — not publish-ready chapters without human edit
